{"title_page": "2001 insurgency in Macedonia", "text_new": "{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict    = 2001 insurgency in Macedonia\n| partof      = the [[Yugoslav Wars]]\n| image       = 2001 Macedonia insurgency.svg\n| image_size  = 315px\n| caption     = \n| date        = 22 January \u2013 12 November 2001<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=01|day1=22|year1=2001|month2=11|day2=12|year2=2001}})\n| place       = [[Polog]] and [[Kumanovo]] regions of the [[North Macedonia|Republic of Macedonia]], near the border with [[Serbia and Montenegro|Yugoslavia]] and [[United Nations Interim Administration Mission in Kosovo|UN-administered]] [[Kosovo and Metohija|Kosovo]].\n| result      = [[Ohrid Agreement]]\n*[[Ceasefire]] established, brokered by [[NATO]]\n*Albanian insurgents agree to disarm\n*The Macedonian government agrees to give greater political rights to Macedonian Albanians\n*Low intensity resurgence since November 2001\n| combatant1  = {{nowrap|{{Flagicon image|Uck Nla logo.svg|border=|size=18px}} [[National Liberation Army (Macedonia)|National Liberation Army]]}}\n| combatant2  = {{flag|Macedonia}}<br />'''Arms support:'''<br />{{flag|Ukraine}}<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.jamestown.org/single/?no_cache=1&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=28044#.VUfxKvmqqko | title=Ukraine Forges Military Alliance with Macedonia | publisher=The Jamestown Foundation | date=31 October 2001 | accessdate=5 May 2015 | last=Kuzio| first=Taras}}</ref><br/>{{flag|Bulgaria}}<ref>{{cite news|last=Lyubomirov |first=Vlad | url=https://www.upi.com/Bulgaria-grants-military-aid-to-Macedonia/69581012337238/ | work=UPI | title=Bulgaria grants military aid to Macedonia | date=29 January 2002}}</ref>\n| commander1  = {{flagicon image|Uck Nla logo.svg|border=|size=16px}} [[Ali Ahmeti]]<br /> {{flagicon image|Uck Nla logo.svg|border=|size=16px}} [[Fadil Nimani]]{{KIA}}<ref name=\"lajmpress.com\">[http://lajmpress.com/lajme/maqedoni/5447.html \"Komandant\u00ebt e U\u00c7K-s\u00eb, disa t\u