38\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0421\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u0410\u043d\u0442\u0438\u045c \u0408\u043e\u0432\u0447\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430 (2004)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.dnevnik.com.mk/default.aspx?pbroj=2431&stID=32243|title=Dnevnik|accessdate=5 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141211065909/http://star.dnevnik.com.mk/default.aspx?pbroj=2431&stID=32243|archive-date=11 December 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n*''My struggle for Macedonia'' by [[Ljube Bo\u0161koski|Ljube Boshkovski]], \u041c\u043e\u0458\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0440\u0431\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0409\u0443\u0431\u0435 \u0411\u043e\u0448\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438 (2004)<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=vBUXAAAACAAJ|title=\u041c\u043e\u0458\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0440\u0431\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=|accessdate=5 December 2014|isbn=9789989572470|last1=\u0411\u043e\u0448\u043a\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0438|first1=\u0409\u0443\u0431\u0435|year=2004}}</ref>\n*''First victim'' by Ljube Profiloski, \u041f\u0440\u0432\u0430 \u0436\u0440\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0409\u0443\u0431\u0435 \u041f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0438\n*NLA terrorist paramilitary in Macedonia by Ivan Babanovski, \u041e\u041d\u0410 \u0442\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0458\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430, \u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d \u0411\u0430\u0431\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438, \u0412\u0415\u0414\u0410, \u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435, 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430\n*Intelligence in counterinsurgency by Aleksandar Iliev, \u0420\u0430\u0437\u0443\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u045a\u0435 \u0432\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0431\u0443\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0432\u043e, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0440 \u0418\u043b\u0438\u0435\u0432, \u041b\u0423\u0411 \u0411\u043b\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0458 \u0408\u0430\u043d\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u041c\u0443\u0447\u0435\u0442\u043e, \u0421\u0442\u0440\u0443\u043c\u0438\u0446\u0430, 2014 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430\n\n====Macedonian authors of Albanian descent====\n\n*''Testimonies of the general'' by [[Gzim Ostreni]], \u0421\u0432\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0448\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0413\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0442 \u043e\u0434 \u0413\u0437\u0438\u043c \u041e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0438<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnevnik.mk/default.asp?ItemID=64F9BFF0FA1CEF4D8E85E090FCF7F5D9|title=\u0413\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u041e\u041d\u0410 \u0413\u0437\u0438\u043c \u041e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u043a\u043d\u0438\u0433\u0430 \u0437\u0430 2001-\u0442\u0430|work=\u0414\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043a|accessdate=5 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141207152746/http://www.dnevnik.mk/default.asp?ItemID=64F9BFF0FA1CEF4D8E85E090FCF7F5D9|archive-date=7 December 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Foreign authors===\n\n*''Fires over Tetovo'' by Rishard Bilski, \u041f\u043e\u0436\u0430\u0440\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0434 \u0422\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043e \u043e\u0434 \u0420\u0438\u0448\u0430\u0440\u0434 \u0411\u0438\u043b\u0441\u043a\u0438 (2003)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kultura.com.mk/BookDetails.aspx?Pr=467 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-06-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606224809/http://www.kultura.com.mk/BookDetails.aspx?Pr=467 |archivedate=6 June 2014 }}</ref>\n*NLA-message and hope by Petrit Menaj, \u041e\u041d\u0410 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0430 \u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0434\u0435\u0436 \u043e\u0434 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0442 \u041c\u0435\u043d\u0430\u0458, \u0424\u043e\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0442 \u043e\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0435\u043d\u043e \u043e\u043f\u0448\u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e, \u041a\u043e\u043c\u0430, \u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435, [http://www.soros.org.mk/CMS/Files/Documents/FIOOM-Poraka-i-nadez-tom-I.pdf 2008]\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|North Macedonia|War}} \n*[[Albanian nationalism (North Macedonia)|Albanian nationalism in North Macedonia]]\n*[[Operation Essential Harvest]]\n*[[Pre\u0161evo valley crisis]]\n*[[2012 Republic of Macedonia inter-ethnic violence]]\n*[[Operation Mountain Storm (Republic of Macedonia)|Operation Mountain Storm]]\n*[[Kumanovo shootings]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{| style=\"margin-left:13px; line-height:150%\"\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:right; vertical-align:top;\"|a.&nbsp;&nbsp;\n|{{note|status}}{{Kosovo-note}}\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20020615010031/http://web.amnesty.org/web/ar2002.nsf/eur/macedonia!Open Casualties and displacement]\n*{{YouTube|d6qdjELcgCI|Macedonian offensive in March and May 2001}}. Video footage of the fighting activities.\n*[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/in_depth/world/2001/review_of_2001/1703711.stm \"Macedonia: Step back from the abyss\"], ''[[BBC]]'', 29 December 2001\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070712033646/http://www.usip.org/pubs/specialreports/sr115.html \"Macedonia: Understanding History, Preventing Future Conflict\"], ''[[United States Institute of Peace]]'', Special Report No. 115, February 2004\n*[http://www.antiwar.com/orig/taylor1.html \"Macedonia's Civil War: 'Made in the USA'\"], ''[[Antiwar.com]]'', 20 August 2001\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20161017230034/http://www.alb-net.com/amcc/articles.htm Chronology of the war]\n*{{YouTube|MD1V59N3K5c|Video of an ethnic standof in Tetovo}} ''[[CTV Television Network|CTV]]''\n*[http://www.marxists.de/balkans/garganas/macedonia.htm Battles \u22129/2001]\n*[http://www.wsws.org/articles/2001/mar2001/mac-m10.shtml Battles \u2013 3/2001]\n*{{cite news|url=http://emperors-clothes.com/news/massing.htm|title=Macedonia on Brink of War|date=10 June 2001|last=Walker|first=Tom|newspaper=[[Sunday Times]]}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070509042555/http://www.antiwar.com/orig/deliso41.html Macedonia On War Footing Over Kosovo Border Provocations]\n*[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/1650954.stm November Battles, Start of War, January 2, 2001]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070311112319/http://archives.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/europe/04/04/macedonia.clash/index.html 2002 attacks]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20131007062608/http://www.antiwar.com/orig/deliso25.html Boskovki interview]\n*[http://www.economist.com/research/backgrounders/displaystory.cfm?story_id=541782 War in the Balkans, again?]\n{{North Macedonia topics}}\n{{Post-Cold War European conflicts}}\n{{Yugoslav wars}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}}\n{{Inter-ethnic clashes in North Macedonia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Insurgency In The Republic Of Macedonia}}\n[[Category:Conflicts in 2001]]\n[[Category:Wars involving North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the Balkans]]\n[[Category:Modern history of North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:2001 in the Republic of Macedonia]]\n[[Category:Insurgencies in Europe]]\n[[Category:2001 insurgency in the Republic of Macedonia| ]]\n[[Category:Ethnic conflicts|Macedonia]]\n[[Category:Albanian separatism]]\n[[Category:Terrorism in North Macedonia]]\n", "name_user": "Keith D", "label": "safe", "comment": "Space", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2001_insurgency_in_Macedonia"}
{"title_page": "Coat of arms of the University of Notre Dame", "text_new": "{{Infobox coat of arms\n|name             = Coat of arms of the University of Notre Dame\n|image            = File:University of Notre Dame coat of arms.svg\n|image_width      = 250\n|middle           = \n|middle_width     = \n|middle_caption   = \n|lesser           = \n|lesser_width     = \n|lesser_caption   = \n|armiger          = [[University of Notre Dame]]\n|year_adopted     = February 13, 1931\n|crest            = none\n|torse            = \n|shield           = ''Azure, a passion cross patty at the extremities Or, issuant of a champagne barry wavy of four Argent and the First, in dexter chief a mullet of six points of the Third, and over all an open book proper charged with the words VITA DULCEDO SPES in letters Sable.'' \n|supporters       = none\n|compartment      = \n|motto            = Vita, Dulcedo, Spes\n|orders           = \n|other_elements   = \n|earlier_versions = \n|use              = \n}}\n\nThe '''coat of arms of the University of Notre Dame''' is the [[Assumed arms|assumed]] [[heraldic achievement]] of the [[University of Notre Dame]].\n\n==History==\nThe coat of arms of the University of Notre Dame was commissioned in early 1931 by university president [[Charles L. O'Donnell|Charles L O\u2019Donnell]], C.S.C.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=RAUCH |first1=R. W. |title=Notre Dame's New Coat of Arms |journal=The Notre Dame Alumnus |date=February 1931 |volume=IX |issue=6 |page=195 |url=http://www.archives.nd.edu/Alumnus/VOL_0009/VOL_0009_ISSUE_0006.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref> The coat of arms was devised by [[Pierre de Chaignon la Rose]], one of America's most prominent heraldrists and designer of the coat of arms of [[Harvard University]]'s Graduate Schools and the [[University of Chicago]] among others.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Official Coat of Arms Adopted for Notre Dame by President |journal=Scholastic |date=February 13, 1931 |volume=64 |issue=16 |url=http://www.archives.nd.edu/Scholastic/VOL_0064/VOL_0064_ISSUE_0016.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=100th anniversary of the University of Chicago seal {{!}} The University of Chicago Library News |url=http://news.lib.uchicago.edu/blog/2012/01/31/100th-anniversary-for-the-university-of-chicago-seal/ |website=news.lib.uchicago.edu |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Heralding a Great University: Pierre de Chaignon la Rose and the Evolution of the Rice Academic Seal |url=https://scholarship.rice.edu/bitstream/handle/1911/88460/wrc04748.pdf?sequence=11&isAllowed=y |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref> He sent his proposed design of armorial bearings in February 1931, and it was immediately accepted and assumed.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Hope |first1=Arthur J. |title=Notre Dame - 100 Years |date=1943 |publisher=University press |location=Notre Dame, Ind. |page=Chapter XXVIII |url=http://archives.nd.edu/hope/hope28.htm}}</ref> The coat of arms, inserted into a circular device with written \"Sigillum Universitatis Dominae Nostrae a Lacu\" became the university seal.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dame |first1=Marketing Communications: Web // University of Notre |title=University Seal // On Message // University of Notre Dame |url=https://onmessage.nd.edu/university-branding/logos/university-seal/#latin |website=On Message |accessdate=16 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nSince 2003, the university relies on a two-colored academic mark consisting of a modified version of the coat of arms, with only two colors, and the official wordmark of the university.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dame |first1=Marketing Communications: Web // University of Notre |title=Academic Mark // On Message // University of Notre Dame |url=https://onmessage.nd.edu/university-branding/logos/academic-mark/ |website=On Message |accessdate=16 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bramanti |first1=Matt |title=Notre Dame releases new icon for usage |url=http://archives.nd.edu/observer/2003-04-25_v37_137.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2019 |date=2003-04-25}}</ref>\n\n==Design==\n\n===Blazon===\n:''Azure, a passion cross patty at the extremities Or, issuant of a champagne barry wavy of four Argent and the First, in dexter chief a mullet of six points of the Third, and over all an open book proper charged with the words VITA DULCEDO SPES in letters Sable.''<ref>{{cite web |title=U.S. Heraldic Registry \u00bb Registrations/Notre Dame, University of |url=http://usheraldicregistry.com/index.php?n=Registrations.20061022S |website=usheraldicregistry.com |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Meaning===\nThe colors blue and gold (azure and gules in heraldry), the official colors of the university, represent Our Lady. The star represents the ancient title of [[Our Lady, Star of the Sea]]. The two wavy lines of silver at the base of the shield, used in heraldry to depict water, are used to represent the two lakes on campus form which the university gets its name (Notre Dame ''Du Lac''). The cross represents the [[Congregation of Holy Cross]], congregation to which university founder [[Edward Sorin]] and following presidents were part of. The open book represents learning and education, and the didactic mission of the university. On its pages is written the motto of the university \"Vita, Dulcedo, Spes,\" from the ancient prayer [[Salve Regina]] meaning \"our life, our sweetness, our hope\".<ref>{{cite journal |last1=RAUCH |first1=R. W. |title=Notre Dame's New Coat of Arms |journal=The Notre Dame Alumnus |date=February 1931 |volume=IX |issue=6 |page=195 |url=http://www.archives.nd.edu/Alumnus/VOL_0009/VOL_0009_ISSUE_0006.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |title=Official Coat of Arms Adopted for Notre Dame by President |journal=Scholastic |date=February 13, 1931 |volume=64 |issue=16 |url=http://www.archives.nd.edu/Scholastic/VOL_0064/VOL_0064_ISSUE_0016.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=U.S. Heraldic Registry \u00bb Registrations/Notre Dame, University of |url=http://usheraldicregistry.com/index.php?n=Registrations.20061022S |website=usheraldicregistry.com |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Other versions==\n<gallery>\nFile:University of Notre Dame seal (3).jpg|Used between 1898 and 1901.\nFile:Second Seal of the University of Notre Dame.png|Used between 1901 and 1930. The seal is derived from the seal of the Congregation of Holy Cross.\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Heraldry]]\n* [[Coat of arms of the University of Chicago]]\n* [[Yale University Coat of Arms]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{University of Notre Dame}}\n\n[[Category:University of Notre Dame]]\n[[Category:Coats of arms of universities in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Infobox coat of arms\n|name             = Coat of arms of the University of Notre Dame\n|image            = File:University of Notre Dame coat of arms.svg\n|image_width      = 250\n|middle           = \n|middle_width     = \n|middle_caption   = \n|lesser           = \n|lesser_width     = \n|lesser_caption   = \n|armiger          = [[University of Notre Dame]]\n|year_adopted     = February 13, 1931\n|crest            = none\n|torse            = \n|shield           = ''Azure, a passion cross patty at the extremities Or, issuant of a champagne barry wavy of four Argent and the First, in dexter chief a mullet of six points of the Third, and over all an open book proper charged with the words VITA DULCEDO SPES in letters Sable.'' \n|supporters       = none\n|compartment      = \n|motto            = Vita, Dulcedo, Spes\n|orders           = \n|other_elements   = \n|earlier_versions = \n|use              = \n}}\n\nThe '''coat of arms of the University of Notre Dame''' is the [[Assumed arms|assumed]] [[heraldic achievement]] of the [[University of Notre Dame]]. \n\n==History==\nThe coat of arms of the University of Notre Dame was commissioned in early 1931 by universiy president [[Charles L. O'Donnell|Charles L O\u2019Donnell]], C.S.C..<ref>{{cite journal |last1=RAUCH |first1=R. W. |title=Notre Dame's New Coat of Arms |journal=The Notre Dame Alumnus |date=February 1931 |volume=IX |issue=6 |page=195 |url=http://www.archives.nd.edu/Alumnus/VOL_0009/VOL_0009_ISSUE_0006.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref> The coat of arms was devised by [[Pierre de Chaignon la Rose]], one of America's most prominent heraldrists and designer of the coat of arms of [[Harvard University]]'s Graduate Schools and the [[University of Chicago]] among others.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Official Coat of Arms Adopted for Notre Dame by President |journal=Scholastic |date=February 13, 1931 |volume=64 |issue=16 |url=http://www.archives.nd.edu/Scholastic/VOL_0064/VOL_0064_ISSUE_0016.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=100th anniversary of the University of Chicago seal {{!}} The University of Chicago Library News |url=http://news.lib.uchicago.edu/blog/2012/01/31/100th-anniversary-for-the-university-of-chicago-seal/ |website=news.lib.uchicago.edu |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Heralding a Great University: Pierre de Chaignon la Rose and the Evolution of the Rice Academic Seal |url=https://scholarship.rice.edu/bitstream/handle/1911/88460/wrc04748.pdf?sequence=11&isAllowed=y |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref> He sent his proposed design of armorial bearings in February 1931, and it was immediately accepted and assumed.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Hope |first1=Arthur J. |title=Notre Dame - 100 Years |date=1943 |publisher=University press |location=Notre Dame, Ind. |page=Chapter XXVIII |url=http://archives.nd.edu/hope/hope28.htm}}</ref> The coat of arms, inserted into a circular device with written \"Sigillum Universitatis Dominae Nostrae a Lacu\" became the university seal.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dame |first1=Marketing Communications: Web // University of Notre |title=University Seal // On Message // University of Notre Dame |url=https://onmessage.nd.edu/university-branding/logos/university-seal/#latin |website=On Message |accessdate=16 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nSince 2003, the university relies on a two-colored academic mark consisting of a modified version of the coat of arms, with only two colors, and the official wordmark of the university.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dame |first1=Marketing Communications: Web // University of Notre |title=Academic Mark // On Message // University of Notre Dame |url=https://onmessage.nd.edu/university-branding/logos/academic-mark/ |website=On Message |accessdate=16 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bramanti |first1=Matt |title=Notre Dame releases new icon for usage |url=http://archives.nd.edu/observer/2003-04-25_v37_137.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2019 |date=2003-04-25}}</ref>\n\n==Design==\n\n===Blazon===\n:''Azure, a passion cross patty at the extremities Or, issuant of a champagne barry wavy of four Argent and the First, in dexter chief a mullet of six points of the Third, and over all an open book proper charged with the words VITA DULCEDO SPES in letters Sable.''<ref>{{cite web |title=U.S. Heraldic Registry \u00bb Registrations/Notre Dame, University of |url=http://usheraldicregistry.com/index.php?n=Registrations.20061022S |website=usheraldicregistry.com |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Meaning===\nThe colors blue and gold (azure and gules in heraldry), the official colors of the university, represent Our Lady. The star represents the ancient title of [[Our Lady, Star of the Sea]]. The two wavy lines of silver at the base of the shield, used in heraldry to depict water, are used to represent the two lakes on campus form which the university gets its name (Notre Dame ''Du Lac''). The cross represents the [[Congregation of Holy Cross]], congregation to which university founder [[Edward Sorin]] and following presidents were part of. The open book represents learning and education, and the didactic mission of the university. On its pages is written the motto of the university \"Vita, Dulcedo, Spes,\" from the ancient prayer [[Salve Regina]] meaning \"our life, our sweetness, our hope\".<ref>{{cite journal |last1=RAUCH |first1=R. W. |title=Notre Dame's New Coat of Arms |journal=The Notre Dame Alumnus |date=February 1931 |volume=IX |issue=6 |page=195 |url=http://www.archives.nd.edu/Alumnus/VOL_0009/VOL_0009_ISSUE_0006.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |title=Official Coat of Arms Adopted for Notre Dame by President |journal=Scholastic |date=February 13, 1931 |volume=64 |issue=16 |url=http://www.archives.nd.edu/Scholastic/VOL_0064/VOL_0064_ISSUE_0016.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=U.S. Heraldic Registry \u00bb Registrations/Notre Dame, University of |url=http://usheraldicregistry.com/index.php?n=Registrations.20061022S |website=usheraldicregistry.com |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Other versions==\n<gallery>\nFile:University of Notre Dame seal (3).jpg|Used between 1898 and 1901.\nFile:Second Seal of the University of Notre Dame.png|Used between 1901 and 1930. The seal is derived from the seal of the Congregation of Holy Cross.\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Heraldry]]\n* [[Coat of arms of the University of Chicago]]\n* [[Yale University Coat of Arms]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:University of Notre Dame]]\n[[Category:Coats of arms of universities in the United States]]\n{{University of Notre Dame}}\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo/generalfixes, replaced: universiy \u2192 university", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coat_of_arms_of_the_University_of_Notre_Dame"}
